th ascend, you don’t get the city’s blessing until it resolves. Players may respond to that spell by trying to change whether you get the city’s blessing.£1/19/2018: If you control ten permanents but don’t control a permanent or resolving spell with ascend, you don’t get the city’s blessing. For example, if you control ten permanents, lose control of one, then cast Golden Demise, you won’t have the city’s blessing and the spell will affect creatures you control.£1/19/2018: If your tenth permanent enters the battlefield and then a permanent leaves the battlefield immediately afterwards (most likely due to the “Legend Rule” or due to being a creature with 0 toughness), you get the city’s blessing before it leaves the battlefield.£1/19/2018: Ascend on a permanent isn’t a triggered ability and doesn’t use the stack. Players can respond to a spell that will give you your tenth permanent, but they can’t respond to getting the city’s blessing once you control that tenth permanent. This means that if your tenth permanent is a land you play, players can’t respond before you get the city’s blessing.£1/19/2018: Some cards have triggered abilities with an intervening “if” clause that checks whether you have the city’s blessing. These are worded “[Trigger condition], if you have the city’s blessing, [effect].” You must already have the city’s blessing in order for these abilities to trigger; otherwise they do nothing. In other words, there’s no way to have the ability trigger if you don’t have the city’s blessing, even if you intend to get it in response to the triggered ability.','B',NULL,'0.01','0.18','1.9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'B','陵墓哈痞','陵墓哈痞','Harpie des mausolées','Harpyie des Mausoleums','Arpia del Mausoleo','霊廟のハーピー','Harpia do Mausoléu','Гарпия Мавзолея','Arpía del mausoleo','영묘 하피','生物 ～哈痞','生物 ～哈痞','Créature : harpie','Kreatur — Harpyie','Creatura — Arpia','クリーチャー ― ハーピー','Criatura — Harpia','Существо — Гарпия','Criatura — Arpía','생물 — 하피','飞行£登殿（如果你操控十个或更多永久物，则于这盘游戏接下